==Translingual==
===Cardinal number===
*[[w:Arabic numerals|Arabic numerals]]: 1
*[[w:Chinese numerals|Chinese numerals]]: 壹, 一
*[[w:Roman numerals|Roman numerals]]: I
===Pronunciation===
''see'' [[one]]
===Noun===
'''1''' (''plural:'' '''[[1s]]''')
# The [[cardinal number]] [[one]], a single thing or unit. 
#:''She only counted '''1'''.''
# [[numeral]] corresponding to the number one.
#:''Formula'' 1 ''racing car''
# A [[digit]] in [[decimal]] and every other [[base]] numbering system, including [[binary]], [[octal]], and [[hexadecimal]].
#:''A binary number ends in'' 1 ''if and only if it is odd.''
#{{mathematics}} the [[identity element]] with respect to [[multiplication]] in a [[ring]].
#: <math>a</math>&times;1=<math>a</math>
#(''computer science'') [[bit]] state corresponding to binary digit 1, or [[on]] or [[true]].
#{{mathematics}} A [[Boolean]] or truth value corresponding to true.
#:''The Boolean domain contains only'' 0 ''and 1.''
